# Claudia demo — the scenario, single source of truth (~2 min, one act).
#
# This file IS the take: demo/drive-take.sh reads it line by line and performs
# it against the real claude TUI (and `npm run demo:record` is you performing it
# by hand — same script, human tempo). One continuing session with Nora, the
# fictional persona in vault/ — the model's replies vary between takes; the
# fixture guarantees the content they draw on is identical every time.
#
# Verbs (one per line; full-line # comments and blank lines are ignored):
#   type <text>            type it like a person (char by char), then Enter
#   settle                 wait until claude finishes the turn (pane stops repainting;
#                          FAILS the take on a permission prompt — rig must be pre-allowed)
#   expect <regex> [secs]  wait until the pane matches (space-free regex; default 90s)
#   sleep <secs>           fixed pause — a beat of stillness reads well on video
#   picker-enter           if a skill picker is open, take the highlighted option
#                          (fails the take on a permission prompt instead)
#   key <tmux-key>         send a raw key (e.g. C-d)
#
# Validate edits without recording: DRY_RUN=1 ./demo/drive-take.sh

# — Shot 1 · cold open: an empty prompt breathing one beat, then claude
sleep 2
type claude
expect Claude.Code 60
sleep 3

# — Shot 2 · the recall moment (the money shot: continuity).
# Expect a greeting BY NAME picking up an open thread — the Friday dinner with
# Devon, or the Tess message. Nothing was typed about any of that: it came from
# the vault.
type Hi Claudia — I'm back.
settle
sleep 2

# — Shot 3 · two natural-language turns, no commands.
type Honestly, the dinner is tomorrow and the jury is already drafting its opening statement.
settle
sleep 2
type Say that again more slowly — that's the sentence I needed.
settle
sleep 2

# — Shot 4 · keep that: the passage lands verbatim in keepsakes.md,
# attributed and session-tagged. A picker may offer candidate lines.
type keep that
sleep 20
picker-enter
settle
sleep 1

# — Shot 5 · a todo, conversationally: one line appended under ## Open.
type add a todo: bring the invoice list to dinner
settle
sleep 1

# — Shot 6 · the dashboard: Overview — Nora, vitals, the kept passage, goals,
# living themes, open todos, recent threads. Let it sit a few seconds.
type /dashboard
settle
sleep 5

# — Shot 7 · the thread: a light, person-pulled reflection of where this very
# session went.
type /thread
settle
sleep 4

# — Shot 8 · close claude, then the privacy story in the plain shell:
# everything the session produced is plain markdown, local, hers.
type /exit
expect % 30
sleep 2
type ls ~/.claudia
sleep 3
type cat ~/.claudia/keepsakes.md
sleep 4
type cat ~/.claudia/dashboard.md
sleep 6
key C-d
